soot.jimple.infoflow.android.callbacks

Class DefaultCallbackAnalyzer

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.callbacks.AbstractCallbackAnalyzer
      • soot.jimple.infoflow.android.callbacks.DefaultCallbackAnalyzer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    soot.jimple.infoflow.memory.IMemoryBoundedSolver

    public class DefaultCallbackAnalyzer
extends AbstractCallbackAnalyzer
implements soot.jimple.infoflow.memory.IMemoryBoundedSolver
    Default implementation of the callback analyzer class. This implementation aims for precision. It tries to rule out callbacks registered in unreachable code. The mapping between components and callbacks is as precise as possible.
    Author:
    Steven Arzt

      • collectCallbackMethods

        public void collectCallbackMethods()
        Collects the callback methods for all Android default handlers implemented in the source code. Note that this operation runs inside Soot, so this method only registers a new phase that will be executed when Soot is next run
        Overrides:
        collectCallbackMethods in class AbstractCallbackAnalyzer

      • checkAndAddMethod

        protected boolean checkAndAddMethod(soot.SootMethod method,
                                    soot.SootMethod parentMethod,
                                    soot.SootClass lifecycleClass,
                                    CallbackDefinition.CallbackType callbackType)
        Description copied from class: AbstractCallbackAnalyzer
        Checks whether the given Soot method comes from a system class. If not, it is added to the list of callback methods.
        Overrides:
        checkAndAddMethod in class AbstractCallbackAnalyzer
        Parameters:
        method - The method to check and add
        parentMethod - The original method in the Android framework that declared the callback. This can, for example, be the method in the interface.
        lifecycleClass - The base class (activity, service, etc.) to which this callback method belongs
        callbackType - The type of callback to be registered
        Returns:
        True if the method is new, i.e., has not been seen before, otherwise false
